### Functions in JavaScript

Functions are blocks of code that can be reused. Here is how you can declare a function:

```javascript
function sayHello() {
  console.log('Hello, World!');
}
```

You can then call this function in your code.

### Loops in JavaScript

Loops are used to repeat a block of code. Here is how you can declare a loop:

```javascript
for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
  console.log(i);
}
```

You can then use this loop in your code.
